SIMPLE: snakehead
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Snakehead
<hw>Snake"head`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
loose, bent-up end of one of the strap rails, or flat rails, formerly
used on American railroads. It was sometimes so bent by the passage of a
train as to slip over a wheel and pierce the bottom of a car.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>The turtlehead.</def>
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>The Guinea-hen flower. See <er>Snake's-head</er>, and
under <er>Guinea</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Snakeneck</ent>⟦br⟧
